So here's the deal with the G2G #46 and CMI #49 entries at the Bristol dirt race according to a TobyChristie.com article: G2G purchased a dirt truck from CMI (a Ford, although G2G typically fields Toyotas) but the chassis wasn't officially transferred, so Tim Viens (the G2G owner) withdrew the #46 and Ray Ciccarelli (the CMI owner) filed a late entry for the #49 for the race. The CMI #49 would have its own owner points: jayski.com/truck-series/2022-ncwts-bristol-dirt-race-owner-points
